comment_data.body:
This will turn off echo by default, which appears to be sensible, isn't it?

```diff
diff --git i/src/nvim/os/pty_process_unix.c w/src/nvim/os/pty_process_unix.c
index bafbfe1e4..a55f1e59d 100644
--- i/src/nvim/os/pty_process_unix.c
+++ w/src/nvim/os/pty_process_unix.c
@@ -57,6 +57,7 @@ int pty_process_spawn(PtyProcess *ptyproc)
   if (!termios_default.c_cflag) {
     // TODO(jkeyes): We could pass NULL to forkpty() instead ...
     init_termios(&termios_default);
+    termios_default.c_lflag &= ~(ECHO);
   }
 
   int status = 0;  // zero or negative error code (libuv convention)
```

How is "not wait for NL or CTRL-D" configured?  (appear to be related to `ICANON`, but without this the job never finishes then)
Also some generic function like `cfmakeraw` might be sensible?
